articles.title: 'Still alive and wriggling:' Doctors remove 3-inch parasitic worm from woman's brain in world first - CNN
articles.description: When a 64-year-old Australian woman was sent to hospital for brain surgery, neurosurgeon Dr. Hari Priya Bandi was not expecting to pull out a live 8-centimeter (3-inch) long parasitic roundworm that wriggled between her forceps.
